<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2014-11-19</DATELINE><TITLE>Microbial sequencing to improve individual and population health</TITLE><BODY>Recent advances in sequencing technologies are changing the face of infectious disease investigation and control. Personalized anti-infective therapies and surveillance of emergent pathogen outbreaks are just two examples of the potential benefits of merging the fields of genomics and infectious diseases.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>